The paper presents an algorithm for training deep neural networks to grasp novel objects, which involves building all the essential components of a grasping system using a forward-backward automatic differentiation approach. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves using 3D shape datasets and collision detection, which are common in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimizing grasp poses, which is a common problem in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing a learning algorithm for grasping systems, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
